Aim

To inspect the dataset using Pandas functions like head(), info(), and describe().

Theory

Data inspection helps to understand dataset structure, column types, and statistical values before analysis.

Software Requirements
Operating System: Windows / macOS / Linux
Anaconda Distribution
Jupyter Notebook
Python 3.x
Pandas Library

Program
import pandas as pd

# Load dataset
df = pd.read_csv('data.csv')

# First five rows
print("First Five Rows:")
print(df.head())

# Dataset information
print("\nDataset Info:")
df.info()

# Statistical summary
print("\nStatistical Summary:")
print(df.describe())


Procedure
Open Jupyter Notebook.
Import Pandas library.
Load CSV dataset using read_csv().
Use head() to display first records.
Use info() to check structure.
View column names and data types.
Use describe() for statistics.
Execute each cell properly.
Observe outputs carefully.
Verify dataset information.


